translate ru strings:

    old "The day of the exam had arrived."
    new "The day of the exam had arrived."

    old "Sarah flexed her muscles, trying to get used to the new suit of armor she was wearing."
    new "Sarah flexed her muscles, trying to get used to the new suit of armor she was wearing."

    old "It had been a gift from Caleb and Ephraim."
    new "It had been a gift from Caleb and Ephraim."

    old "Sarah was eager for any chance to improve her odds of passing the exam and had gladly accepted it."
    new "Sarah was eager for any chance to improve her odds of passing the exam and had gladly accepted it."

    old "It had been a gift from Kate, one of her old suits of armor."
    new "It had been a gift from Kate, one of her old suits of armor."

    old "A large crowd had gathered to watch the recruits that were attempting the exam today."
    new "A large crowd had gathered to watch the recruits that were attempting the exam today."

    old "Sarah had begun to understand that the exam was half actual exam, and half social event for the mercenaries."
    new "Sarah had begun to understand that the exam was half actual exam, and half social event for the mercenaries."

    old "She had stood off to the side, watching recruit after recruit apply."
    new "She had stood off to the side, watching recruit after recruit apply."

    old "So far, out of the twelve participants, seven had managed to pass. The others failed."
    new "So far, out of the twelve participants, seven had managed to pass. The others failed."

    old "More than half, Sarah figured, for motivation."
    new "More than half, Sarah figured, for motivation."

    old "But now her time of observing had come to an end, and it was her turn."
    new "But now her time of observing had come to an end, and it was her turn."

    old "She heard her name called out, and she strode onto the open arena."
    new "She heard her name called out, and she strode onto the open arena."

    old "All around her, she heard the cheers and howls of the soldiers. Standing at the center of their attention began to make her nervous."
    new "All around her, she heard the cheers and howls of the soldiers. Standing at the center of their attention began to make her nervous."

    old "Sarah knew she was ready, but still she felt a pit in her stomach. Would she really pass? What if she made a fool out of herself in front of everyone?"
    new "Sarah knew she was ready, but still she felt a pit in her stomach. Would she really pass? What if she made a fool out of herself in front of everyone?"

    old "Sarah had borrowed from Kate an old suit of armor and a sword that probably didn't cut much, but was heavy enough to bash someone with."
    new "Sarah had borrowed from Kate an old suit of armor and a sword that probably didn't cut much, but was heavy enough to bash someone with."

    old "She turned around, her eyes scanning the crowd."
    new "She turned around, her eyes scanning the crowd."

    old "Amidst the crowd, she found Kate."
    new "Amidst the crowd, she found Kate."

    old "Kate smiled at her, in a way that could make Sarah feel like she was exactly where she had to be."
    new "Kate smiled at her, in a way that could make Sarah feel like she was exactly where she had to be."

    old "Sarah knew she was ready, but she felt a pit in her stomach. Would she really pass? What if she made a fool out of herself in front of everyone?"
    new "Sarah knew she was ready, but she felt a pit in her stomach. Would she really pass? What if she made a fool out of herself in front of everyone?"

    old "Amidst the crowd, she found Atilla."
    new "Amidst the crowd, she found Atilla."

    old "The orc stood, towering above everyone around him, his arms crossed. To most, his gaze was the same, one of barely contained rage."
    new "The orc stood, towering above everyone around him, his arms crossed. To most, his gaze was the same, one of barely contained rage."

    old "But Sarah knew Atilla, and she could see that he was telling her to be strong."
    new "But Sarah knew Atilla, and she could see that he was telling her to be strong."

    old "For him, she knew she could."
    new "For him, she knew she could."

    old "She was grateful that he had not yet left the camp, but stuck around to watch her attempt the exam."
    new "She was grateful that he had not yet left the camp, but stuck around to watch her attempt the exam."

    old "Amidst the crowd, she found Caleb and Ephraim."
    new "Amidst the crowd, she found Caleb and Ephraim."

    old "Caleb and Ephraim were both smiling at her."
    new "Caleb and Ephraim were both smiling at her."

    old "Once Sarah made eye contact, Caleb began cheering, throwing his hands up."
    new "Once Sarah made eye contact, Caleb began cheering, throwing his hands up."

    old "They made an odd trio."
    new "They made an odd trio."

    old "But Sarah felt comfort, seeing her new friends here."
    new "But Sarah felt comfort, seeing her new friends here."

    old "She might doubt herself, but she knew that neither Caleb nor Ephraim did. And that made her feel the doubt slip away."
    new "She might doubt herself, but she knew that neither Caleb nor Ephraim did. And that made her feel the doubt slip away."

    old "Sarah straightened her back and brought out her shoulders. Whatever doubt she might have had, she would make them invisible to the world."
    new "Sarah straightened her back and brought out her shoulders. Whatever doubt she might have had, she would make them invisible to the world."

    old "Across from her was the man conducting the exam."
    new "Across from her was the man conducting the exam."

    old "She had watched him spar with each of the previous participants. He didn't seem to have even begun to break a sweat."
    new "She had watched him spar with each of the previous participants. He didn't seem to have even begun to break a sweat."

    old "Still, Sarah could see that he had begun to measure himself. He was more cautious with his swings, reserving his energy."
    new "Still, Sarah could see that he had begun to measure himself. He was more cautious with his swings, reserving his energy."

    old "If she had gone first, she might not have had a chance, but now, she could imagine an opening."
    new "If she had gone first, she might not have had a chance, but now, she could imagine an opening."

    old "She knew she didn't need to beat him, noone so far had, all that was required was a good showing."
    new "She knew she didn't need to beat him, noone so far had, all that was required was a good showing."

    old "Still, she wanted to."
    new "Still, she wanted to."

    old "Next participant, Sarah Rose..."
    new "Next participant, Sarah Rose..."

    old "Are you ready?"
    new "Are you ready?"

    old "Sarah unsheated her sword. With both hands wrapped around the handle, she held it up in front of herself."
    new "Sarah unsheated her sword. With both hands wrapped around the handle, she held it up in front of herself."

    old "Still a dull training blade, she told herself she would soon earn a real one."
    new "Still a dull training blade, she told herself she would soon earn a real one."

    old "Ready!"
    new "Ready!"

    old "Sarah found herself declaring, louder than first expected."
    new "Sarah found herself declaring, louder than first expected."

    old "Off to the side of the grounds, somewhere in the crowd, a bell was rung."
    new "Off to the side of the grounds, somewhere in the crowd, a bell was rung."

    old "Immediately, the examinator began to advance."
    new "Immediately, the examinator began to advance."

    old "Sarah noticed his broad steps, how he held up his sword, ready to strike. There was no hestitation."
    new "Sarah noticed his broad steps, how he held up his sword, ready to strike. There was no hestitation."

    old "Everything before this had been training matches."
    new "Everything before this had been training matches."

    old "This was the first battle, the first fight, that Sarah could actually lose, that meant anything."
    new "This was the first battle, the first fight, that Sarah could actually lose, that meant anything."

    old "Too late, Sarah realized her mistake."
    new "Too late, Sarah realized her mistake."

    old "Whilst she had stood her ground, the examinator had closed the distance."
    new "Whilst she had stood her ground, the examinator had closed the distance."

    old "With the crowd close to her back, Sarah found herself cornered."
    new "With the crowd close to her back, Sarah found herself cornered."

    old "The examinator pulled his arm back, before releasing a sweeeping blow aimed at Sarah's midriff."
    new "The examinator pulled his arm back, before releasing a sweeeping blow aimed at Sarah's midriff."

    old "Just in time, Sarah managed to drop her blade to her side, defending herself from the attack."
    new "Just in time, Sarah managed to drop her blade to her side, defending herself from the attack."

    old "As the examinator's blade connected, Sarah felt herself being thrown off balance, tumbling across the ground."
    new "As the examinator's blade connected, Sarah felt herself being thrown off balance, tumbling across the ground."

    old "All her practice kicked in, a voice reminded her to get off the ground, or everything would be over."
    new "All her practice kicked in, a voice reminded her to get off the ground, or everything would be over."

    old "Moving with her tumbling motion, she quickly managed to get back onto her foot, only to find the examinator up close."
    new "Moving with her tumbling motion, she quickly managed to get back onto her foot, only to find the examinator up close."

    old "He wasn't going to let her take her time."
    new "He wasn't going to let her take her time."

    old "But, Sarah realized, that had been her mistake from the start, thinking she could take her time."
    new "But, Sarah realized, that had been her mistake from the start, thinking she could take her time."

    old "The examinator released another blow, same as the last, but this time, Sarah was ready."
    new "The examinator released another blow, same as the last, but this time, Sarah was ready."

    old "She slid down to the ground, diving under the blade, hearing it cut the air above her head, missing by an inch."
    new "She slid down to the ground, diving under the blade, hearing it cut the air above her head, missing by an inch."

    old "Sarah thrusted the tip of her blade forward, towards the examinator's knees."
    new "Sarah thrusted the tip of her blade forward, towards the examinator's knees."

    old "He stepped to avoid her blade, but Sarah had not expected to hit him, she only wanted to interrupt his rhythm."
    new "He stepped to avoid her blade, but Sarah had not expected to hit him, she only wanted to interrupt his rhythm."

    old "As the examinator focused on avoiding her jabs at his feet, she quickly spun around him."
    new "As the examinator focused on avoiding her jabs at his feet, she quickly spun around him."

    old "Sarah looked around, the large open space was now behind her. Here, her speed was an advantage."
    new "Sarah looked around, the large open space was now behind her. Here, her speed was an advantage."

    old "The examinator began pushing forward, swinging wildly, trying to break free from the corner."
    new "The examinator began pushing forward, swinging wildly, trying to break free from the corner."

    old "Sarah decided to let him, hopping back just outside of the reach of his blade."
    new "Sarah decided to let him, hopping back just outside of the reach of his blade."

    old "Each barely missed strike only seemed to further the examinator's rage."
    new "Each barely missed strike only seemed to further the examinator's rage."

    old "Despite his heavy armor and the large sword, he suddenly seemed to leap."
    new "Despite his heavy armor and the large sword, he suddenly seemed to leap."

    old "It would have caught Sarah by surprise, but she had seen him do something similar before. She knew he could be faster than he appeared, and she had been waiting for it."
    new "It would have caught Sarah by surprise, but she had seen him do something similar before. She knew he could be faster than he appeared, and she had been waiting for it."

    old "Rather than surprising Sarah, the examinator found himself surprised when the princess dove low, under his blade, and leaping forward, driving her blade into his stomach."
    new "Rather than surprising Sarah, the examinator found himself surprised when the princess dove low, under his blade, and leaping forward, driving her blade into his stomach."

    old "Sarah felt her blade slide through the cracks in the examinator's armor, and pressing into his body."
    new "Sarah felt her blade slide through the cracks in the examinator's armor, and pressing into his body."

    old "He jolted, his hands began to reach for her."
    new "He jolted, his hands began to reach for her."

    old "But with the blade now lodged in the crack, Sarah used it like a wedge."
    new "But with the blade now lodged in the crack, Sarah used it like a wedge."

    old "Pushing the handle up, she leveraged the examinator off his feet."
    new "Pushing the handle up, she leveraged the examinator off his feet."

    old "Once pushed off balance, the weight of his armor pulled him down to the ground."
    new "Once pushed off balance, the weight of his armor pulled him down to the ground."

    old "A loud crashing sound echoed across the training ground as the examinator, his armor and his massive blade, crashed into the ground."
    new "A loud crashing sound echoed across the training ground as the examinator, his armor and his massive blade, crashed into the ground."

    old "Sarah found herself temporarily blinded by the dust, thrown up by his fall."
    new "Sarah found herself temporarily blinded by the dust, thrown up by his fall."

    old "But all around her, she heard the thundering cheers of the observers."
    new "But all around her, she heard the thundering cheers of the observers."

    old "The crowd began to howl and cheer."
    new "The crowd began to howl and cheer."

    old "As the dust parted, Sarah found herself standing over her opponent, one foot firmly planted on the examinator's chest, her blade still sticking into his armor and exposed body."
    new "As the dust parted, Sarah found herself standing over her opponent, one foot firmly planted on the examinator's chest, her blade still sticking into his armor and exposed body."

    old "Looking through the man's visor, she thought she could see a smile."
    new "Looking through the man's visor, she thought she could see a smile."

    old "The examinator only rose one arm, and threw up his thumb."
    new "The examinator only rose one arm, and threw up his thumb."

    old "The crowd exploded into another cacophony of cheers."
    new "The crowd exploded into another cacophony of cheers."

    old "Members of the crowd surged onto the training ground and began to seize Sarah's limbs."
    new "Members of the crowd surged onto the training ground and began to seize Sarah's limbs."

    old "Sarah felt herself being pulled up, lifted off the ground by the many hands on her body."
    new "Sarah felt herself being pulled up, lifted off the ground by the many hands on her body."

    old "She was hoisted onto a man's shoulders."
    new "She was hoisted onto a man's shoulders."

    old "From atop his shoulders, she looked out over the crowd. All around her, cheering, happy faces, raised arms, celebrating her victory."
    new "From atop his shoulders, she looked out over the crowd. All around her, cheering, happy faces, raised arms, celebrating her victory."

    old "One voice began."
    new "One voice began."

    old "Rose Knight!"
    new "Rose Knight!"

    old "And others followed."
    new "And others followed."

    old "Rose Knight! Rose Knight! Rose Knight!"
    new "Rose Knight! Rose Knight! Rose Knight!"

    old "Soon everyone present was chanting her title."
    new "Soon everyone present was chanting her title."

    old "Sarah began to wave her arms, embracing their adulations. This only seemed to drive the crowd wilder."
    new "Sarah began to wave her arms, embracing their adulations. This only seemed to drive the crowd wilder."

    old "Sarah felt her arm being grabbed, and she looked down."
    new "Sarah felt her arm being grabbed, and she looked down."

    old "There she saw Kate's face, looking up at her, smiling."
    new "There she saw Kate's face, looking up at her, smiling."

    old "Sarah smiled back at Kate, smiled in a way she hadn't for a long time, holding back nothing."
    new "Sarah smiled back at Kate, smiled in a way she hadn't for a long time, holding back nothing."

    old "Still atop the man's shoulders, she grabbed and pulled on Kate's arm."
    new "Still atop the man's shoulders, she grabbed and pulled on Kate's arm."

    old "The crowd, understanding in the way that crowd's can, raised Kate up to Sarah."
    new "The crowd, understanding in the way that crowd's can, raised Kate up to Sarah."

    old "Sarah wrapped her hands around Kate's face and drew her into a deep kiss."
    new "Sarah wrapped her hands around Kate's face and drew her into a deep kiss."

    old "As they carried her further, Sarah let Kate slide from her hands, back into the crowd."
    new "As they carried her further, Sarah let Kate slide from her hands, back into the crowd."

    old "Kate's eyes scanned the crowd, searching for Atilla, but she could not find him."
    new "Kate's eyes scanned the crowd, searching for Atilla, but she could not find him."

    old "It dawned on her that she might very well have seen him for the last time."
    new "It dawned on her that she might very well have seen him for the last time."

    old "A soft melancholy infected her moment of glory."
    new "A soft melancholy infected her moment of glory."

    old "Joy and sadness seemed to exist in her heart at the same time."
    new "Joy and sadness seemed to exist in her heart at the same time."

    old "Amongst the many faces and hands, she recognized Caleb and Ephraim, cheering her on."
    new "Amongst the many faces and hands, she recognized Caleb and Ephraim, cheering her on."

    old "She smiled at them, glad to have made them proud."
    new "She smiled at them, glad to have made them proud."

    old "While the win had settled it, the official declaration followed later that day."
    new "While the win had settled it, the official declaration followed later that day."

    old "Sarah had passed the exam."
    new "Sarah had passed the exam."

    old "Most of the celebrations had turned the rest of the day into a blur."
    new "Most of the celebrations had turned the rest of the day into a blur."

    old "She found herself standing in Vaelen's tent."
    new "She found herself standing in Vaelen's tent."

    old "Vaelen was sitting behind his desk, papers strewn about."
    new "Vaelen was sitting behind his desk, papers strewn about."

    old "Sarah observed him, the quiet confidence he exuded whilst sitting in the chair reminded her of someone."
    new "Sarah observed him, the quiet confidence he exuded whilst sitting in the chair reminded her of someone."

    old "Her father, she later realized."
    new "Her father, she later realized."

    old "He too had seemed so perfectly content in the role that life had placed on him."
    new "He too had seemed so perfectly content in the role that life had placed on him."

    old "Sarah wondered about her own role to play."
    new "Sarah wondered about her own role to play."

    old "Not that long ago, she was able to see everything. Support her brother Thomas, be married to some noble, raise his children..."
    new "Not that long ago, she was able to see everything. Support her brother Thomas, be married to some noble, raise his children..."

    old "But fate, Sarah had come to know, enjoyed making a ruin of such plans."
    new "But fate, Sarah had come to know, enjoyed making a ruin of such plans."

    old "She was a princess without a nation, cast across the sea, trying to find her way home again."
    new "She was a princess without a nation, cast across the sea, trying to find her way home again."

    old "Once more, in her heart, she defied fate and allowed herself to dream a path."
    new "Once more, in her heart, she defied fate and allowed herself to dream a path."

    old "You did quite well on the exam, I heard."
    new "You did quite well on the exam, I heard."

    old "The Rose Knight...I think they're calling you..."
    new "The Rose Knight...I think they're calling you..."

    old "It's just a silly name, I'm sure they will move on soon."
    new "It's just a silly name, I'm sure they will move on soon."

    old "Vaelen shrugged."
    new "Vaelen shrugged."

    old "Perhaps...perhaps not. A boy once joined our company, and on exam day he threw up on himself."
    new "Perhaps...perhaps not. A boy once joined our company, and on exam day he threw up on himself."

    old "I think they called him splot for years after, never lived it down."
    new "I think they called him splot for years after, never lived it down."

    old "Well, I suppose there are worse names, should it stick."
    new "Well, I suppose there are worse names, should it stick."

    old "Vaelen pushed a sheet of paper from his desk towards Sarah."
    new "Vaelen pushed a sheet of paper from his desk towards Sarah."

    old "For some that join, they need someone to read out the words, but I imagine you know how to read?"
    new "For some that join, they need someone to read out the words, but I imagine you know how to read?"

    old "Her eyes scrolled across the paper. A contract, really."
    new "Her eyes scrolled across the paper. A contract, really."

    old "Signing it meant a minimum of five years in service of the Brothers of Providence. For five years, they would be her home."
    new "Signing it meant a minimum of five years in service of the Brothers of Providence. For five years, they would be her home."

    old "It was what she had wanted, and yet, she still found herself doubting, for a brief moment."
    new "It was what she had wanted, and yet, she still found herself doubting, for a brief moment."

    old "Once she signed, her new life would truly begin."
    new "Once she signed, her new life would truly begin."

    old "Sarah steeled herself, grabbing a pen and quickly drawing her royal signature."
    new "Sarah steeled herself, grabbing a pen and quickly drawing her royal signature."

    old "She pushed the contract back at Vaelen."
    new "She pushed the contract back at Vaelen."

    old "Do you remember what we spoke about, months ago when we first met?"
    new "Do you remember what we spoke about, months ago when we first met?"

    old "Vaelen sat up straight."
    new "Vaelen sat up straight."

    old "I do...I vowed that I would help you return to Rosanna."
    new "I do...I vowed that I would help you return to Rosanna."

    old "Sarah looked straight at him."
    new "Sarah looked straight at him."

    old "Do you still intend to keep that promise?"
    new "Do you still intend to keep that promise?"

    old "Vaelen paused for a moment, before nodding."
    new "Vaelen paused for a moment, before nodding."

    old "I don't have much of a choice."
    new "I don't have much of a choice."

    old "He leaned in further."
    new "He leaned in further."

    old "I'm sure you've heard the story from some, but I don't walk a normal path."
    new "I'm sure you've heard the story from some, but I don't walk a normal path."

    old "Sarah said nothing, but she did remember Kate having briefly spoken about it."
    new "Sarah said nothing, but she did remember Kate having briefly spoken about it."

    old "A long time ago, when I was still young, younger than you even, I lived in a small town out in the Mytrhan Southlands."
    new "A long time ago, when I was still young, younger than you even, I lived in a small town out in the Mytrhan Southlands."

    old "Nothing grows there, it's mostly desert."
    new "Nothing grows there, it's mostly desert."

    old "The only way that anyone makes a living, is by working the mines. And in the Southlands, you begin working the mines early."
    new "The only way that anyone makes a living, is by working the mines. And in the Southlands, you begin working the mines early."

    old "I was eleven years old, had been working the mines for some years at that point."
    new "I was eleven years old, had been working the mines for some years at that point."

    old "The children were tasked with exploring the deeper parts, given that we were so small, only we could fit through the crevices."
    new "The children were tasked with exploring the deeper parts, given that we were so small, only we could fit through the crevices."

    old "Vaelen rasped his knuckles across the desk."
    new "Vaelen rasped his knuckles across the desk."

    old "One day, that started the same as any other, we went back into the mines and I crawled through one of the crevices."
    new "One day, that started the same as any other, we went back into the mines and I crawled through one of the crevices."

    old "Each path lead into the next, and with each step, the corridor grew more narrow. That is when I made my fatal mistake."
    new "Each path lead into the next, and with each step, the corridor grew more narrow. That is when I made my fatal mistake."

    old "Growing afraid, I turned too fast and my body became lodged, fixed, between the walls of the cavern."
    new "Growing afraid, I turned too fast and my body became lodged, fixed, between the walls of the cavern."

    old "I could still cry out, but I could no longer move my body, trapped in the rock."
    new "I could still cry out, but I could no longer move my body, trapped in the rock."

    old "Some of the other children found me, but none of the adults could reach me. They tried to pull me free, but I was too stuck."
    new "Some of the other children found me, but none of the adults could reach me. They tried to pull me free, but I was too stuck."

    old "And so, after their attempts were exhausted, they left to go back to the surface, and I was left alone, in the depths of the earth, in the pitch black."
    new "And so, after their attempts were exhausted, they left to go back to the surface, and I was left alone, in the depths of the earth, in the pitch black."

    old "Vaelen threw up his hands."
    new "Vaelen threw up his hands."

    old "Ooh Sarah, never did I know a darkness that black could exist."
    new "Ooh Sarah, never did I know a darkness that black could exist."

    old "Unable to sleep, still trapped, all I could do was remain. I lost any sense of time..."
    new "Unable to sleep, still trapped, all I could do was remain. I lost any sense of time..."

    old "But eventually, the darkness itself began to stir. The nothingness began to shift and take shape."
    new "But eventually, the darkness itself began to stir. The nothingness began to shift and take shape."

    old "Soon after, the voices began. At first, unintelligible, but slowly, the words began to make sense to me."
    new "Soon after, the voices began. At first, unintelligible, but slowly, the words began to make sense to me."

    old "There, trapped, the darkness reached out and spoke to me, but it did not frighten me, Sarah, rather, it soothed."
    new "There, trapped, the darkness reached out and spoke to me, but it did not frighten me, Sarah, rather, it soothed."

    old "Like my mother, it carassed my head, whispered my name with a voice full of love, and it began to tell me of a world that could be."
    new "Like my mother, it carassed my head, whispered my name with a voice full of love, and it began to tell me of a world that could be."

    old "Trapped in that mine, I began to see visions of every corner of the world. There, at the bottom of the mine, I saw the ocean before I had ever seen it with my own eyes."
    new "Trapped in that mine, I began to see visions of every corner of the world. There, at the bottom of the mine, I saw the ocean before I had ever seen it with my own eyes."

    old "And slowly, the void and the voices strung these visions together in a narrative. The great narrative of my life."
    new "And slowly, the void and the voices strung these visions together in a narrative. The great narrative of my life."

    old "It told me what I could become, what the stars themselves had decreed for me."
    new "It told me what I could become, what the stars themselves had decreed for me."

    old "Sarah felt her breath slow, hearing Vaelen's tale."
    new "Sarah felt her breath slow, hearing Vaelen's tale."

    old "I saw everything that I had to do, all that I would do, and all that would ever come to pass."
    new "I saw everything that I had to do, all that I would do, and all that would ever come to pass."

    old "Vaelen pointed directly at Sarah."
    new "Vaelen pointed directly at Sarah."

    old "And you...Sarah Rose...long before you came to my camp I knew we would meet."
    new "And you...Sarah Rose...long before you came to my camp I knew we would meet."

    old "And I knew that I would have to aid you in reclaiming your country."
    new "And I knew that I would have to aid you in reclaiming your country."

    old "Vaelen stood up, walked around the table and grabbed Sarah by the shoulders."
    new "Vaelen stood up, walked around the table and grabbed Sarah by the shoulders."

    old "Sarah...we are walking along a sacred path. Every moment is as fixed as the stars in heaven."
    new "Sarah...we are walking along a sacred path. Every moment is as fixed as the stars in heaven."

    old "And I can see it all around you...we live a charmed life, Sarah, trust me in that, if nothing else."
    new "And I can see it all around you...we live a charmed life, Sarah, trust me in that, if nothing else."

    old "Sarah found her voice to speak."
    new "Sarah found her voice to speak."

    old "Then what comes next?"
    new "Then what comes next?"

    old "Vaelen laughs."
    new "Vaelen laughs."

    old "Too much to speak of, would that I could, but we must live fate, not speak it."
    new "Too much to speak of, would that I could, but we must live fate, not speak it."

    old "With this..."
    new "With this..."

    old "Vaelen held up Sarah's contract."
    new "Vaelen held up Sarah's contract."

    old "We've set our first steps."
    new "We've set our first steps."

    old "Feeling overwhelmed, Sarah excused herself and stepped outside."
    new "Feeling overwhelmed, Sarah excused herself and stepped outside."

    old "The cold air washed over her face. It reminded her of home."
    new "The cold air washed over her face. It reminded her of home."

